<para id="element-40">We find that work by friction in rolling is zero. It is so because it does negative work in translation and equal positive work in rotation. There may be situations in which friction does positive work in translation and negative work in rotation. For example, if a body is initially given  angular velocity greater than linear velocity required by equation of rolling, then the friction does the positive work in translation (accelerates translation) and negative work in rotation (decelerates rotation). Here also, net work by friction is zero in rolling.
</para>
