<section id="section-5">
<title> Summary
</title>
<para id="element-83">
<term>1: </term> Work by friction is zero in rolling.
</para>
<para id="element-84">
<term>2: </term> Work by friction in translation and rotation are equal in magnitude but opposite in direction.
</para>
<para id="element-85">
<term>3: </term> Gravitational potential energy change in rolling motion is due to change in position of the COM due to translation – not rotation.
</para>
<para id="element-86"><term>4: </term> The rolling has both kinetic energies corresponding to translation and rotation. The distribution of kinetic energy between two motions depend on the distribution of moment of inertia as :
</para>
<para id="element-87">
